---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { TEST_STATS } from '../lib/testStats';

const repoUrl = 'https://github.com/timjstacey/resume-static-site';

const projectRows = [
  { project: 'content', device: 'Desktop Chrome', specs: 'home, jobs, projects, resume' },
  { project: 'a11y-chromium', device: 'Desktop Chrome', specs: 'nav, theme-picker' },
  { project: 'a11y-firefox', device: 'Desktop Firefox', specs: 'nav, theme-picker' },
  { project: 'a11y-webkit', device: 'Desktop Safari', specs: 'nav, theme-picker' },
  { project: 'responsive-mobile-chrome', device: 'Pixel 5', specs: 'responsive' },
  { project: 'responsive-mobile-safari', device: 'iPhone 13', specs: 'responsive' },
  { project: 'responsive-tablet-safari', device: 'iPad Pro 11', specs: 'responsive' },
];

const ciRows = [
  { workflow: 'ci.yml', steps: 'check-claude-md.sh → pnpm lint → pnpm test → pnpm typecheck → pnpm build' },
  { workflow: 'playwright.yml', steps: 'Wait for Cloudflare Pages preview deploy → run E2E against the preview URL' },
];
---

<Base title="Testing" description="Test automation strategy for this site">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-ctp-text">Testing</h1>
  <p class="mt-2 text-ctp-subtext1">
    This site is a working demo of how I run test automation. Two layers (vitest for data and logic, Playwright for
    rendered pages) gate every merge to <code class="text-ctp-mauve">main</code>.
  </p>

  <section aria-label="Test stats" class="mt-6 grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 sm:grid-cols-4">
    <div class="rounded-lg border border-ctp-surface1 bg-ctp-mantle p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-ctp-mauve">{TEST_STATS.unit}</p>
      <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-ctp-subtext0">Unit tests</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg border border-ctp-surface1 bg-ctp-mantle p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-ctp-blue">{TEST_STATS.e2e}</p>
      <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-ctp-subtext0">E2E specs</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg border border-ctp-surface1 bg-ctp-mantle p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-ctp-green">{TEST_STATS.projects}</p>
      <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-ctp-subtext0">Playwright projects</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-lg border border-ctp-surface1 bg-ctp-mantle p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-ctp-peach">{TEST_STATS.engines}</p>
      <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-ctp-subtext0">Browser engines</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ctp-text">Test pyramid</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-ctp-subtext1">
      Vitest handles the cheap checks. Playwright handles anything needing real DOM, layout, or keyboard input.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-4 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-ctp-surface1 bg-ctp-mantle p-5">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-ctp-text">Unit (vitest)</h3>
        <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-sm text-ctp-subtext1">
          <li>
            Zod schema parsing for <code class="text-ctp-mauve">resume.yml</code>,
            <code class="text-ctp-mauve">projects.yml</code>, <code class="text-ctp-mauve">jobs.yml</code>
          </li>
          <li>Date formatting, pipeline stats, nav active-path logic</li>
          <li>
            Fixture invariants (e.g. <code class="text-ctp-mauve">jobs.yml</code> must contain at least one Applied entry,
            required by the filter E2E spec)
          </li>
          <li>Full suite runs in ~300 ms locally</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-lg border border-ctp-surface1 bg-ctp-mantle p-5">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-ctp-text">E2E (Playwright)</h3>
        <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-sm text-ctp-subtext1">
          <li>Page rendering driven by YAML data, not hardcoded fixtures</li>
          <li>Mobile drawer focus trap and theme picker keyboard handling</li>
          <li>Responsive overflow checks at 375 px viewport</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ctp-text">Project routing</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-ctp-subtext1">
      Running every spec on every browser duplicated work. Splitting by spec type cut total runs from ~415 to
      {TEST_STATS.e2e}.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-4 overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full border-collapse text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-ctp-surface1 text-left text-ctp-subtext0">
            <th class="py-2 pr-4 font-medium">Project</th>
            <th class="py-2 pr-4 font-medium">Device</th>
            <th class="py-2 font-medium">Specs</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {
            projectRows.map((row) => (
              <tr class="border-b border-ctp-surface0">
                <td class="py-2 pr-4 font-mono text-ctp-mauve">{row.project}</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4 text-ctp-subtext1">{row.device}</td>
                <td class="py-2 text-ctp-subtext1">{row.specs}</td>
              </tr>
            ))
          }
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-ctp-subtext1">
      Content DOM is identical across engines, so it runs once. Keyboard and focus differ between engines, so a11y specs
      run on all three. Layout depends on viewport, so responsive runs on mobile and tablet devices.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ctp-text">Data-driven everything</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-ctp-subtext1">
      Specs import the same YAML loaders the site uses. Adding a job to <code class="text-ctp-mauve">jobs.yml</code>
      adds a card-rendering E2E. Renaming a status in the enum breaks the spec at typecheck, not runtime.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-2 text-ctp-subtext1">
      Shared constants between components and tests (theme flavors, nav items, status labels) live in
      <code class="text-ctp-mauve">src/lib/</code>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ctp-text">CI gates</h2>

    <div class="mt-4 overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full border-collapse text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-ctp-surface1 text-left text-ctp-subtext0">
            <th class="py-2 pr-4 font-medium">Workflow</th>
            <th class="py-2 font-medium">Steps</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {
            ciRows.map((row) => (
              <tr class="border-b border-ctp-surface0">
                <td class="py-2 pr-4 font-mono text-ctp-mauve">{row.workflow}</td>
                <td class="py-2 text-ctp-subtext1">{row.steps}</td>
              </tr>
            ))
          }
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 mb-12">
    <a href={repoUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-sm text-ctp-blue hover:text-ctp-text">
      Source on GitHub →
    </a>
  </section>
</Base>
